{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #629: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. The list chromatic number $\\chi_L(G)$ is defined to be the minimal $k$ such that for any assignment of a list of $k$ colours to each vertex of $G$ (perhaps different lists for different vertices) a colouring of each vertex by a colour on its list can be chosen such that adjacent vertices receive distinct colours.\n\nDetermine the minimal number of vertices $n(k)$ of a bipartite graph $G$ such that $\\chi_L(G)>k$. Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.","id":"vf_060fb056d1361da9","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Partial result.","id":"vf_5b74967819b2c8f5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/629.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_060fb056d1361da9","source_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","target":"erdos:629","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_5b74967819b2c8f5","source_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","target":"erdos:629","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143","frontier_root":"sha256:a4d62c3b7a2ca0a02a1bf4ce1b4ad0ffb06b6f2f61ff9f5b58ed8ee07d8b2bf1","label":"Erdős 629","lenses":{"all_authored":false,"current_record":false,"mathematical_work":false,"research_plus_scouting":false},"lifecycle":"unstarted","location":"reference_only","machine_status":"not_checked","mathematical_scope":"not_applicable","method_channels":[],"node